snippet.textDisplay: OK Casey. I've followed you from the early days. This particular record of you enjoying such extortionate luxury is NOT what I've been used to observing or wanting to view on your channel. You've lost your focus boy by becoming something you 'personally' may have aspired to but, for the most part of your audience I suspect, you have lost them on your journey. Well done Casey if this is what you consider the zenith of you life. But, please, please don't disrespect the many millions of people who have followed your path who will not get anywhere close to your personal aspirations. As a 70 year old man who has way more life experience you can ever amount to so far, believe me, you may lose your audience by the bucketload if you continue to publish such inane, extravagant productions in the future. OK, you American's extol such luxury, such extravagance. That might be fine for your 'home crowd'; but you have reached out to millions in your 'poor and pauper' days - including me in the UK who really, really enjoyed your 'poverty'  groundbreaking days. I'm afraid you're losing touch Casey; from a whole bunch of people who followed you avidly. But nothing lasts forever.
